      "message": "Just thinking: returning \"nil\" from a Context-modifier can be problematic. If an error occurs, someone may accidentally assign/reuse \"c\" to log that error and cause a problem.\n\ne.g.,\n\nvar err error\nif c, err \u003d lucictx.SwitchLocalAccount(c, \"whatever\"); err !\u003d nil {\n  logging.Errorf(c, \"failed to do something: %s\", err)\n  return...\n}\n\nThe \"c\" in the logging statement will be nil/invalid and panic.\n\nElsewhere, we\u0027ve done by-reference passing of pointers to error methods:\n\nif err :\u003d lucictx.SwitchLocalAccount(\u0026c, \"whatever\"); err !\u003d nil { ... }\n\nAlternatively, you could return original \"ctx\" here. I\u0027d just not return \"nil\".",
